<br>
Don't you think they are trying to work things out as best they can? This person here is crying out for his problem to be fixed while that person there wants his done, while the person who can play the game OK is complaining about the broken quest and another is about class balance. Little wonder things appear to be in chaos, and I ask you, do you seriously think that Verant can help that most of it occurs? If you can run a company of that size with such an unstable product as online software without any flaws then I'll take notice. Just because your problems aren't being fixed or that they are also developing other services doesn't mean that they aren't working on it. It would be foolish to devote everyone in the company to CS.<br>
<br>
Posted on the PoN forums:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I find it absolutely hilarious that folks think that since EQ makes about 7 million a month that Verant/Sony is rolling in all this money.<br>
<br>
I find it even MORE hilarious that folks are all upset abou this new service. What Verant is not supposed to make money or something? COME ON! WAKE UP! This is there BUSINESS! Since when is running a BUSINESS and making MONEY wrong?!<br>
<br>
Lets look at the numbers:<br>
<br>
38 Servers. Each Server is roughly 27 computers/servers farmed together. So rought 1026 Computers that had to be bought, installed, configured, upgraded, maintained and serviced on a regular basis as they run 24/7. <br>
<br>
Then there is the power to run that many PC's and then the BANDWIDTH needed to accomodate EQ and it's 60,000+ nightly players.<br>
<br>
Then there is the Rental of floor/office space to house the equiment.<br>
<br>
Then there is SPARE hardware for emergency repairs/raid drive swapping.<br>
<br>
Then there is office space for EMPPLOYESS that has to be rented.<br>
<br>
Then Insurance for the equipment and office space.<br>
<br>
Then Payroll for say 45 employees on project development, management, code writing, content creation.<br>
<br>
Then say another 50 full time GM's for the servers.<br>
<br>
Then there is advertising and travel costs and employee benfits costs, along with taxes and such.<br>
<br>
If you assume 100 employees from Gm's all the way to the CEO of Verant and assume an AVERAGE of 40,000 dollars a year salary (which realistically is probabaly pretty damn low), payroll alone is 4,000,000 year. Now add in employee benefits cost, management costs, overhead etc and your spending a HELL OF a lot more money than you guys apparently are taking into consideration.<br>
<br>
Hell a 2hour MOVIE theses days costs 10 dollars. Fro those of you playing EQ for 8+ hours a day you sure as hell are getting your monies worth off 10 measly bucks.<br>
<br>
Hell 10 bucks won't even fill a gas tank or buy you a good meal out any more.<br>
<br>
Before you scream that all these added online features should be free think about how much it will costs to give the services they are stating in the new Legends service.<br>
<br>
24/7 Support from FULL gm's. That alone is at least triple standard payroll for that. A team of Content GM's to make and run on a REGULAR Basis the new dynamic events that they promise. New servers and server code for the online data features, tech's to maintain them, Bandwitdth to accomadate the web access, Insurance for Equipment and personel, additional payroll nad benefits cost, additional floor and office space, additional electric bills.<br>
<br>
Assuming 8000 subscribers at 40 bucks a pop your lokking at only an additional 320,000 a month for this server.<br>
<br>
Oh and I bet they would like to make a PROFIT too on this. After all anyone who runs a BUSINESS should. Not like it is wrong to.<br>
<br>
Will I go to it? Not sure. It is attractive, but all my friends are on bertoxx. Unless I could convince the majority to go I would say no.<br>
<br>
Had this been avaialble at the start i am sure I would have gone with it though.<br>
<br>
But screaming that all these additional services should be included now is just silly and ludicrous.<br>
<br>
Some folks are never satisfied and some simply have no idea what it takes to run a business in the REAL world. <br>
<br>
Gilfalas Elaandrin<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Personally I think EQLegends will not only be a success, it will be good for the common servers as well. I ask you, even if EQLegends was never planned doy you think that your CS would improve? Do you think they would fix everything? I don't. It may just be that EQLegends is the first step towards it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Taliewin Lifesworde<br>
Divine Fellowship<br>
Half Elf Paladin of the 48th Rank<br>
Mith Marr Server<br>
