<br>
If the GMs had turned the guides loose more often to do GM events, then there might be more people guiding for the fun of it and the players would be generally happier. Water under the bridge.<br>
<br>
So, this is VI's answer.  Web page?  Bah, there are free profile utilties out there already.  CS?  I seldom need a guide/gm for anything anymore and I really don't expect one to answer when I do.  If they do answer, I don't expect them to do what I feel is the correct thing.  I don't even know who our GM is or if we have one and I could not name one guide right now.  I don't think I have seen one in a year.<br>
<br>
Guild halls?  Cool.  More events, maybe cool.  Not $40 per month cool.<br>
<br>
I do feel that we are justified in being a little irked by some of the Luclin things which are still not working as promised when clearly a lot of resources have been diverted to the Legends project.<br>
